headline: Trump Has Taken Control Over These Companies. How Their Stocks Have Fared.
summary: President Donald Trump is exerting an unprecedented amount of control over private companies.  Companies that need something from the White House have found the help comes with strings attached.  Trump in June approved  Nippon Steel’s  purchase of U.S. Steel, but only in exchange for veto power over some corporate actions.
